Two motorcyclists, believed to be in their 40s, died when their bikes collided head-on on the R704 near Bloemfontein on Saturday afternoon, Free State paramedics said. The collision took place past the Piet Odendaal Road, about 20km from Bloemfontein, ER24 spokesperson Annine Dormehl said. ER24 paramedics were first to arrive at the scene at 2pm, where they found both motorbikes burning. The road had to be closed for cleaning and local authorities were on the scene for further investigation, Dormehl said. February 11 &#8211; Two motorcyclists, believed to be in their 40s, died when their bikes collided head-on on the R704 near Bloemfontein on Saturday afternoon. Both bikes caught alight. Photo: ER24 African News Agency (ANA) For more news your way, follow The Citizen on Facebook and Twitter. For more news your way, follow The Citizen on Facebook and Twitter.